Godswill Akpabio, one of the ministers sworn-in by President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday was caught partying and dancing immediately after the inauguration. Akpabio, a former Governor of Akwa Ibom State, was one of the 43 ministers assigned portfolios yesterday at the Presidential Villa. He was assigned the ministry of Niger Delta Affairs as the senior minister. The former lawmaker was seen partying on the streets of Abuja immediately after he took the oath of office. In one of the videos obtained by DAILY POST, the former lawmaker could be seen dancing alongside a popular musician, MC Galaxy. Senator Akpabio and his political associates partied through the evening of Wednesday. Watch video below…   I think Senator #Godswillakpabio parties more than any other #Buhari's newly appointed #Ministers after their swearing-in on Wednesday A post shared by  nwachukwu john owen (@realjohn_owen) on Aug 21, 2019 at 11:35pm PDT    Ladies and gentlemen, behold your Minister of Niger Delta Affairs #Godswillakpabio #nigerians #nigeriangovernment #NDDC A post shared by  nwachukwu john owen (@realjohn_owen) on Aug 21, 2019 at 12:49pm PDT  Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.